                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Positivism refers to the application of the scientific method to the social world; the birth of sociology. LO 2.1 Explain what culture is, how culture provides orientations to life, and what practicing cultural relativism means."
                },
                "answer_1": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Cultural leveling refers to the process by which cultures become similar to one another. Justin is experiencing a drastically different culture that has him feeling disoriented. LO 2.1 Explain what culture is, how culture provides orientations to life, and what practicing cultural relativism means."
                },
                "answer_4": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: We receive negative sanctions when we break social norms. In this case Justin is not breaking a social norm, he is witnessing a culture starkly different from his own. LO 2.1 Explain what culture is, how culture provides orientations to life, and what practicing cultural relativism means."
